# Task 3: Machine Learning Implementation & MLflow Tracking

This document summarizes the results of the Machine Learning experiments conducted on the student performance dataset.

## 🚀 Accomplishments

- **Multi-Algorithm Implementation**: Successfully implemented and tuned KNN, SVM, Random Forest, and Logistic Regression.
- **MLflow Integration**: Tracked all experimental runs (parameters, metrics, and models) using MLflow.
- **Dimensionality Reduction**: Applied PCA and t-SNE for data visualization and evaluated model performance on reduced feature sets.
- **Results Analysis**: Extracted and compared performance metrics across all models to identify the best approach.

## 📊 Model Comparison

| Model | Parameters | Accuracy | F1-Score | Precision | Recall |
|-------|------------|----------|----------|-----------|--------|
| **Logistic Regression** | C=10.0 | **0.9646** | 0.9692 | 0.9735 | 0.9649 |
| **SVM** | kernel=linear, C=1.0 | **0.9646** | 0.9694 | 0.9652 | 0.9737 |
| **Random Forest** | n_estimators=100, max_depth=None | 0.9596 | 0.9649 | 0.9649 | 0.9649 |
| **KNN** | k=3 | 0.9343 | 0.9432 | 0.9391 | 0.9474 |
| **RF (PCA-Reduced)** | n_estimators=100, features=5 | 0.9242 | N/A | N/A | N/A |

